            <h3><a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/12/18/global-geomorphologic-map-of-titan/index.html">Global Geomorphologic Map of Titan</a></h3>
            <hr />
            
                
                    
                        
                            
<a href="media/GlobalGeomorphologicMapofTitan.jpg" rel="lightbox"></a>
    
        <img src="media/GlobalGeomorphologicMapofTitan.jpg" style="max-width:100%; max-height:100%;"class="articlelrg" alt="Image credit: None">
    

                        
                    
                        
                            <p>	<p>The first global geomorphologic map of Titan has been published.</p>

	<p>Titan’s thick and hazy atmosphere has hindered the identification of its geologic features at visible wavelengths, so scientists combined all the available datasets from Cassini (<span class="caps">RADAR</span>, <span class="caps">VIMS</span>, <span class="caps">ISS</span>) to create the map. Correlations between datasets enabled them to produce a global map even where datasets were incomplete.</p>

	<p>Titan has an active methane-based hydrologic cycle that has shaped a complex geologic landscape, making its surface one of most geologically diverse in the Solar System. Despite the differences in materials, temperatures and gravity fields between Earth and Titan, many of their ...</p></p>
                        
                    
                
            

            
                <p>Source: [<a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41550-019-0917-6">Nature Geosciences</a>]</p>
            
            <p>
                <a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/12/18/global-geomorphologic-map-of-titan/index.html">Read More</a>
            </p>
            <div class="post-info">
                <div class="category-tray">
                
                    
                        <a href="index.html#"><img src="static/img/icon/research-highlights.gif" alt="Research Highlights" align="top"/></a>
                    
                
