        <li>
            <h3><a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/12/13/molecular-cousins-discovered-on-titan/index.html">Molecular Cousins Discovered on Titan</a></h3>
            <hr />
            
                
                    
                        
                            
<a href="media/apjlab3860f1_lr.jpg" rel="lightbox"></a>
    
        <img src="media/apjlab3860f1_lr.jpg" style="max-width:100%; max-height:100%;"class="articlelrg" alt="Neutral C1, C2, and C3 hydrocarbons of Titan&#39;s atmosphere and their approximate volume mixing ratios at 200 km derived. Credit: Vinatier et al. (2015). Image credit: None">
        <br>
        <span>Neutral C1, C2, and C3 hydrocarbons of Titan's atmosphere and their approximate volume mixing ratios at 200 km derived. Credit: Vinatier et al. (2015).</span>
    

                        
                    
                        
                            <p>	<p>The atmosphere of Titan, the largest moon of Saturn, is rich in organic molecules, and it has been suggested that the moon may serve as an analog for the pre-biotic Earth due to its highly reducing chemistry and existence of global hazes. Photochemical models of Titan have predicted the presence of propadiene (historically referred to as allene), CH<sub>2</sub><span class="caps">CCH</span><sub>2</sub>, an isomer of the well-measured propyne (also called methylacetylene) CH<sub>3</sub><span class="caps">CCH</span>, but its detection has remained elusive due to insufficient spectroscopic knowledge of the molecule.</p>

	<p>The <i>Cassini</i> spacecraft explored the Saturn system from 2004 through 2017, during which ...</p></p>
                        
                    
                
            

            
                <p>Source: [<a href="https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.3847/2041-8213/ab3860">The Astrophysical Journal Letters</a>]</p>
            
            <p>
                <a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/12/13/molecular-cousins-discovered-on-titan/index.html">Read More</a>
            </p>
            <div class="post-info">
                <div class="category-tray">
                
                    
                        <a href="index.html#"><img src="static/img/icon/research-highlights.gif" alt="Research Highlights" align="top"/></a>
                    
                
