        <li>
            <h3><a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/8/12/scientists-discover-a-new-method-for-exploring-europas-extraterrestrial-ocean/index.html">Scientists Discover a New Method for Exploring Europa’s Extraterrestrial Ocean</a></h3>
            <hr />
            
                
                    
                        
                            
<a href="media/pia19048.jpg" rel="lightbox"></a>
    
        <img src="media/pia19048.jpg" style="max-width:100%; max-height:100%;"class="articlelrg" alt="Europa&#39;s stunning surface, which may hold clues to the characteristics of the oceans hidden underneath. Image Credit: NASA/JPL-Caltech/SETI Institute Image credit: None">
        <br>
        <span>Europa's stunning surface, which may hold clues to the characteristics of the oceans hidden underneath. Image Credit: NASA/JPL-Caltech/SETI Institute</span>
    

                        
                    
                        
                            <p>	<p>Earth is a world of astonishing biodiversity. Yet, despite the extreme variety of lifeforms on our planet, there is one key trait all life here shares: none of it can survive without water. This is why, when scientists scour the cosmos for potentially habitable worlds, the presence of liquid water is one of the most alluring traits a celestial object can exhibit.</p>

	<p>390 million miles away from Earth, an icy moon harbors an abundance of liquid water just below its frozen surface. Jupiter’s moon Europa is home to an extraterrestrial sea that’s billions of years old, and may ...</p></p>
                        
                    
                
            

            
                <p>Source: [<a href="https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0019103518304275">Icarus</a>]</p>
            
            <p>
                <a rel="bookmark" href="articles/2019/8/12/scientists-discover-a-new-method-for-exploring-europas-extraterrestrial-ocean/index.html">Read More</a>
            </p>
            <div class="post-info">
                <div class="category-tray">
                
                    
                        <a href="index.html#"><img src="static/img/icon/research-highlights.gif" alt="Research Highlights" align="top"/></a>
                    
                
                </div>
                <span class="post-info-date">
                    August 12, 2019 &bullet; 
                    
                        Written by: Glorie Martinez
                    
                    &bullet; <a href="articles/3743/report-issue/index.html">Report issue</a>
                </span>
